cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper focuses on shared resource management in multicore systems, specifically memory and cache interference. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), which deals with the design and analysis of computer systems. The paper also proposes memory scheduling techniques, which falls under cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes models for quantifying the impact of interference on application performance, which could fall under cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper proposes use cases for improving performance and fairness, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
